class="c13"><span id="iii.ix.xvii-p14.3"></span>mss.</span> of Eusebius
give the name. In Justin the form <span class="Greek"><span
id="iii.ix.xvii-p14.4"></span>᾽</span><span class="Greek"><span
id="iii.ix.xvii-p14.5"></span>Ούρβικος</span> occurs, which is a direct
transcription of the Latin *Urbicus.*

